lopment?\").\n* [15]\n  D. Rein, B. L. Hou, A. C. Stickland, J. Petty, R. Y. Pang, J. Dirani, J. Michael, and S. R. Bowman (2024)\n  GPQA: a graduate-level google-proof q&a benchmark.\n  In First Conference on Language Modeling,\n  External Links: [Link](https://openreview.net/forum?id=Ti67584b98)\n  Cited by: [Appendix C](#A3.SS0.SSS0.Px2.p1.2 \"Domain 2: Graduate-Level Science (GPQA/HLE). ‣ Appendix C Detailed Domain Instantiations ‣ The Meta-Agent Challenge: Are Current Agents Capable of Autonomous Agent Development?\").\n* [16]\n  J. Schmidhuber (2003)\n  Gödel machines: self-referential universal problem solvers making provably optimal self-improvements.\n  arXiv preprint cs/0309048.\n  Cited by: [§1](#S1.p4.1 \"1 Introduction ‣ The Meta-Agent Challenge: Are Current Agents Capable of Autonomous Agent Development?\").\n* [17]\n  Harbor Framework\n  External Links: [Link](https://github.com/laude-institute/harbor)\n  Cited by: [Appendix C](#A3.SS0.SSS0.Px4.p1.2 \"Domain 4: Code Agent (SWE-Bench). ‣ Appendix C Detailed Domain Instantiations ‣ The Meta-Agent Challenge: Are Current Agents Capable of Autonomous Agent Development?\"),\n  [§4](#S4.SS0.SSS0.Px1.p1.1 \"Meta-Agent Systems. ‣ 4 Experimental Setup ‣ The Meta-Agent Challenge: Are Current Agents Capable of Autonomous Agent Development?\").\n* [18]\n  W. Wang, X. Xu, X. Xu, et al. (2025)\n  Let it flow: agentic crafting on rock and roll, building the rome model within an open agentic learning ecosystem.\n  External Links: 2512.24873,\n  [Link](https://arxiv.org/abs/2512.24873)\n  Cited by: [Appendix C](#A3.SS0.SSS0.Px5.p1.2 \"Domain 5: Terminal Agent (Terminal-Bench). ‣ Appendix C Detailed Domain Instantiations ‣ The Meta-Agent Challenge: Are Current Agents Capable of Autonomous Agent Development?\").\n* [19]\n  X. Wang, B. Li, Y. Song, F. F. Xu, X. Tang, M. Zhuge, J. Pan, Y. Song, B. Li, J. Singh, et al. (2024)\n  Openhands: an open platform for ai software developers as generalist agents.\n  arXiv preprint a